		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=560"><span id=>Milquetoast</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br>10 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Milquetoast&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>There are a few places where you can rake in the experience at your level Adail.&nbsp;&nbsp;Steamfont is an excellent place to start.  Between the haunted ruins with the static spawning skeletons, the earth elementals, harpies, drakes, giant clockworks, and the minotaur slavers...it's a great place to level that is normally not overly crowded.  <br><br>Lavastorm would be good with at least another person.  Fire elementals, rock dervishes, and fire imps also give great experience.<br><br>If you want to hunt closer to a town zone, there is always the Northern Desert of Ro.  There you can fight mummies, madmen(beware the casters), giant scarabs, and the ever popular Cutthroat Dervishes.  The cutthroats are normally camped and you may have to wait to get into a group.  The bronze loot however makes this wait well worth your while.<br><br>After you gain a couple of levels and get your 14 spells, I would either go to the Oasis, Western Commonlands, or brave the Karana plains.  I would really hold off on going to the Karanas until you become mana efficient with your new guns.<br><br>I hope this helps and wish you the best of luck.<br></p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Milquetoast Outland<br>Druid of Tunare-Karana</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
