		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=1497"><span id=>Madisun</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br>8 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Madisun&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Another option you may also want to try is Blackburrow for there are plenty of mobs at your level. There is generally a good mix of race/class folks in the zone (to group, if you so&nbsp;&nbsp;     ).  The best experience of all comes during the trips you make to sell the loot you gathered in the zone...you have the chance to run accross a Rabid Grizzly and score yourself at least half-a-bub experience for one kill!  Just take the rabid pelt to the priestess (not sure of name) in the UFO in Qeynos.  She will reward you with a ton of experience, 1 or 2pp, and a spell that sells for 6+ gp with average charisma. (as another bonus you can use the spell that you get for turning in the pelt-- its a level 19 spell Endure Disease)<br><br>After you get to level 14, go and purchase the anti-summoned spell and sow and head to Lavastorm.  IF you can handle the downtime (it was approx 6-8 min for me depending on the creature's resists) you will soar to 17 (18 if you can be patient).  My method was to med in the tunnel past the broken door that leads to Najena.  Make sure you have sow up, skin like&lt;blank&gt;, &lt;blank&gt;coat, and whatever other buffs you can afford...then find a lava crawler, fire imp (careful they are more difficult), or other summoned creature (go to eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com for a breakdown of the summoned mobs at that level) and learn to kite.  I did not use levitate as I generally ran the mob in a pentagon style pattern right in front of Najena, kiting with the anti-summon all the way.  Fair loot at that level...but awesome experience both in the leveling aspect and also (and more importantly) the "learn to kite" aspect.  The later will get you through life as a druid under any number of circumstances.<br><br>I hope this helps to get you on your way.<br>Happy Hunting<br>Madisun </p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Madisun Padisun - Retired<br>Master Baker, Brewer, Fletcher, Potter,<br>Smith, Jeweller, and Tailor</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
